  "texts": [
    "This process involves invertible transitions between random noises to the target data distribution.",
    "The forward process, termed the diffusion step, incrementally introduces noise to the original input.",
    "Conversely, the reverse process, labeled the denoising step, counteracts the forward process, reconstructing data samples from the noises.",
    "In this study, we employ two variants of diffusion-based models.",
    "The first is a 1D denoising diffusion probabilistic model 51, hereafter termed \"1Ddiffusion,\" and the second is a diffusion language model 52, referred to as \"diffusion-LM\" in subsequent discussions."
  ],
